  "doc_id": "11388",
  "text": "RNA extraction and Northern blot analysis. Total cellular RNA was isolated from confluent cell cultures or from freshly isolated murine brain using a commercially available kit (RNAzolB) based on the single step guanidinium-isothiocyanate method [CITATION_1] . Polyadenylated RNA was selected by oligo-dT-cellulose spin columns and precipitated with ethanol in the presence of glycogen. Messenger RNA was separated by electrophoresis in 1% agarose formaldehyde gels, transferred to nylon membranes, and fixed by heating at 80 Њ C under vacuum for 2 h. Blots were probed with radiolabeled cDNAs for the rat CNTFR ␣ (33) or the housekeeping gene Cho-B [CITATION_2] 34) , and analyzed using a PhosphorImager (Molecular Dynamics, Sunnyvale, CA).",
